{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1f2e3d4-0011-4c22-9a33-5b6c7d8e9f01",
    "name": "KYC Service",
    "description": "Every endpoint of the **KYC Service** (`apps/kyc-service`) — the applicant-onboarding REST API.\n\nBase URL variable: `kycBaseUrl` (default `http://localhost:8080`).\n\n## Demo order\n\nRun the **Applicants** folder top to bottom. The three \"Register\" requests are crafted to produce the three screening outcomes once the Screening Service processes their events:\n\n| Request | Name / country | Screening decision |\n|---------|----------------|--------------------|\n| Register — CLEARED | Amina Yusuf / SD | `CLEARED` |\n| Register — REVIEW | Reza Karimi / IR (high-risk) | `REVIEW` |\n| Register — BLOCKED | John Doe / US (watchlist) | `BLOCKED` |\n\nThe CLEARED request also sets an `X-Correlation-Id` and asserts the service echoes it back — the same id is copied into the Kafka event, so you can grep both services' logs for one onboarding. The created id is saved into `applicantId` for the GET requests below.\n\nSee `apps/postman/README.md` for the full Day-1 demo script.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Applicants",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register applicant — CLEARED (201)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Mint a correlation id so we can follow this onboarding across both services.",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('correlationId', 'demo-' + pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}'));"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Location header points at the new applicant', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Location')).to.match(/\\/applicants\\/\\d+$/);",
                  "});",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('new applicant starts PENDING', () => pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('PENDING'));",
                  "pm.test('correlation id is echoed back', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('X-Correlation-Id')).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('correlationId'));",
                  "});",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('applicantId', body.id);",
                  "pm.environment.set('applicantId', body.id);",
                  "console.log('Registered applicant', body.id, 'correlationId', pm.collectionVariables.get('correlationId'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Correlation-Id", "value": "{{correlationId}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fullName\": \"Amina Yusuf\",\n  \"nationalId\": \"SD-1990-000123\",\n  \"dateOfBirth\": \"1990-04-12\",\n  \"country\": \"SD\",\n  \"email\": \"amina.yusuf@example.com\",\n  \"attributes\": {\n    \"channel\": \"mobile\",\n    \"branch\": \"khartoum\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kycBaseUrl}}/applicants",
              "host": ["{{kycBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["applicants"]
            },
            "description": "Registers a clean applicant. Returns `201` + `Location` and the `ApplicantResponse` (status `PENDING`). Persists the applicant and an outbox row in one transaction; the outbox dispatcher then publishes an `applicant-registered` event to Kafka. After screening, this one is **CLEARED**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Register applicant — REVIEW (201)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('starts PENDING', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('PENDING'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fullName\": \"Reza Karimi\",\n  \"nationalId\": \"IR-1988-554120\",\n  \"dateOfBirth\": \"1988-09-30\",\n  \"country\": \"IR\",\n  \"email\": \"reza.karimi@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kycBaseUrl}}/applicants",
              "host": ["{{kycBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["applicants"]
            },
            "description": "Country `IR` is on the (illustrative) high-risk list, so after screening this applicant needs manual **REVIEW** with a raised risk score. The KYC API itself still returns `201 PENDING` — the decision happens downstream in the Screening Service."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Register applicant — BLOCKED (201)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('starts PENDING', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('PENDING'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fullName\": \"John Doe\",\n  \"nationalId\": \"US-1979-110078\",\n  \"dateOfBirth\": \"1979-01-15\",\n  \"country\": \"US\",\n  \"email\": \"john.doe@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kycBaseUrl}}/applicants",
              "host": ["{{kycBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["applicants"]
            },
            "description": "The name \"John Doe\" is on the (fake) sanctions/PEP watchlist, so after screening this applicant is **BLOCKED** with risk score 100. Again, the KYC API returns `201 PENDING`; the watchlist hit is decided by the Screening Service."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Register applicant — invalid (400)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('400 Bad Request', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('uniform ApiError body with per-field violations', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('status', 400);",
                  "    pm.expect(body.violations).to.be.an('array').that.is.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('names the offending fields', () => {",
                  "    const fields = body.violations.map(v => v.field).join(',');",
                  "    pm.expect(fields).to.include('fullName');",
                  "    pm.expect(fields).to.include('email');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fullName\": \"\",\n  \"nationalId\": \"\",\n  \"dateOfBirth\": \"2999-01-01\",\n  \"country\": \"\",\n  \"email\": \"not-an-email\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kycBaseUrl}}/applicants",
              "host": ["{{kycBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["applicants"]
            },
            "description": "Breaks every Bean Validation rule: blank `fullName`/`nationalId`/`country`, a future `dateOfBirth` (`@Past`), a malformed `email`. `ValidationExceptionMapper` turns the `ConstraintViolationException` into a `400` with a uniform `ApiError` listing each field."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get applicant by id (200)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('returns the applicant we registered', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().id).to.eql(Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('applicantId')));",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kycBaseUrl}}/applicants/{{applicantId}}",
              "host": ["{{kycBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["applicants", "{{applicantId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Reads back the applicant created by \"Register applicant — CLEARED\" using the saved `applicantId`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get applicant — not found (404)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('404 Not Found', () => pm.response.to.have.status(404));",
                  "pm.test('uniform ApiError body', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('status', 404));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kycBaseUrl}}/applicants/999999",
              "host": ["{{kycBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["applicants", "999999"]
            },
            "description": "An unknown id. `ApplicantNotFoundExceptionMapper` returns `404` with the same uniform `ApiError` shape."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List applicants (paged)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('returns a JSON array', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kycBaseUrl}}/applicants?page=0&size=20",
              "host": ["{{kycBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["applicants"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size", "value": "20" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Newest-first paginated listing via `@QueryParam`/`@DefaultValue` (`page` defaults to `0`, `size` to `20`). After the three registrations above you should see all three applicants."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "The applicant onboarding API: `POST /applicants`, `GET /applicants/{id}`, `GET /applicants`."
    },
    {
      "name": "Health & metrics",
